reviewText: The matches that stood out was taka vs pantera and classic main event!The rest of the ppv was mid card raw matches.The main event was awesome with a whole heeps of weapons including barb wire which was wrapped around cactus jack ....surprise surprise.......at start it was a mad brawl then quited down in to great tag action..The highlight of that match was when austin picked up the bin in his corner and pegged it at billy gunn an got him right in the face.Overall if you are a big wwf fan this for you for the main event only, if you are just getting into the wwf i would select a newer ppv such as wrestlemania 17, but by all meens do try and watch this some how!
summary: GREATEST TAG MAIN EVENT YOU WILL SEE
Title: WWF No Way Out! - In Your House VHS

reviewText: What was this!? This whole PPV was pathetic! Every match was terrible, some matches I had to fast forward through because they where so boring they almost made me go to sleep! The main event was the only good match on the whole card, while all the others where horrible.
Title: WWF No Way Out! - In Your House VHS

reviewText: Alrighty if you are reading this then you should know this is a review for a retro wrestling Pay Per View & my last review was for The Royal Rumble 1998 & after a solid show I am taking a look if The WWF put on a good follow up or did they just treat this as a throwaway B level show. I am pretty sure that you found this review randomly & were just interested in what  people though of this show or you grew up during this time period of Professional Wrestling like me. Or you never got to experience what happened in the past & are curious. I'll go into the backstory in what lead up to some of the important matches. On The January 19th episode of RAW IS WAR Vince McMahon was going to make a huge announcement about Mike Tyson's role at Wrestlemania XIV. Stone Cold Steve Austin interrupted & told Mike Tyson off Tyson shoved Austin official's had to hold Austin down. The following week on RAW IS WAR Stone Cold challenged Mike Tyson to show up at No Way Out. Shawn Michaels pushed for Austin vs Tyson to get out of defending The WWF Championship at Wrestlemania XIV. Meanwhile on this episode of RAW IS WAR Triple H was suppose to defend The WWF European Championship against Owen Hart. Hunter sent out The Artist Formally Known As Goldust disguised as himself. Owen won the match & Commissioner Slaughter announced Owen Hart as the new European Champion. The following week on RAW IS WAR Shawn Michaels & Triple H came out like they were at a political convention Austin reminded Shawn Michaels that he won The Royal Rumble & he has to defend the title against him. It was also announced that DeGeneration X would team up with The New Age Outlaws to face Stone Cold Steve Austin Owen Hart Cactus Jack & Chainsaw Charlie at No Way Out. On this same episode Chainsaw Charlie & Cactus Jack were in the middle of a hardcore match while they were both in a Dumpster The New Age Outlaws showed up shut & locked the lid on The Dumpster & pushed it off the stage. This was so well done it was believable cause you had both heels & faces mad at The New Age Outlaws. Shawn & Hunter told them that is how you get ratings & attention. They planned to throw Owen Hart off the stage but they were stopped by officials. Stone Cold took on Jesse James were DX came out to help The Outlaws they tied Austin up on the ring ropes & Shawn Michaels put The WWF Championship in front of him he told him this is close as you'll get to it. Cactus Jack & Chainsaw Charlie returned from the hospital & Terry Funk still had his hospital gown on but they ran DX & The Outlaws off. The next week on RAW IS WAR Stone Cold Steve Austin called Shawn Michaels out but he refused to meet him in the ring. Austin told him that he stole his title belt Michaels checked his bag where keeps The WWF title he found a toy replica DX went to look for Austin Chyna got The Los Boricus to help them Stone Cold locked them in a room. At the end of the show DX came out Shawn Michaels called Stone Cold out he was cornered by DeGeneration X & The New Age Outlaws but from under the ring Chainsaw Charlie, Cactus Jack & Owen came out when Chainsaw Charlie cut hole in the ring. So the heels fled but not before Chyna grabbed The WWF title belt. On The January 26th episode of RAW IS WAR Kane attacked Big Van Vader & gave him The Tombstone Piledriver. The next week on RAW IS WAR Vader took a Fire Extinguisher which blinded Kane in his only good eye. On The January 19th episode of RAW IS WAR Barry Windham turned on Bradshaw to join Jim Cornette's NWA faction.  effectively ending The New Blackjacks should've been done sooner cause The New Blackjackss  u  c  ked. On The January 26th episode of RAW IS WAR Pantera defeated Brian Christopher to face Taka Michinouku for The WWF Lightheavyweight Championship at this show & that is pretty much the backstory for this Pay Per View. The buyrate was a 0.52 that is up from In Your House 13 that got a 0.50 but the No Way Out buyrate was a big drop off from The Royal Rumble that is understandable seeing as The Royal Rumble is a big show & No Way Out is a B level show.The current champions in The WWF wereWWF Champion Shawn Michaels November 9th 1997WWF Intercontinental Champion The Rock December 8th 1997 The Rock was awarded the title when Stone Cold Steve Austin who was Champion at the time refused to defend the title in a mandatory title defense.WWF European Champion Owen Hart January 20th 1998 aired January 26th 1998 Owen Hart defeated Goldust who was disguised as Triple H Commissioner Slaughter allowed the title to change handsWWF Tag Team Champions The New Age Outlaws Road Dogg Jesse James & BA Billy GunnNovember 24th 1997WWF Lightheavyweight Champion Taka Michinoku December 7th 1997Date February 15, 1998Attendance 16,110Venue Compaq CenterCity Houston, TexasFree For AllThey announce that Shawn Michaels will not compete due to a back injury.A great video package is shown for The Kane VS Vader match.Sunny interviewed Vader he said that Kane will be destroyed here tonight he asked Sunny what time is it & she said about 15 minutes away from The Pay Per View. Kevin Kelly was in The A O L Room he asked Jim Cornette who he thinks will replace Shawn Michaels in The 8 Man Tag Cornette didn't care cause it had nothing to do with The NWA.The New Age Outlaws cut a promo on their recent actions but Cactus Jack & Chainsaw Charlie are after them.A very good video package is shown for The 8 Man Tag.Dok Hendrix tried to talk to Triple H but he was busy with a phone call.Then we get to The Pay Per ViewThe Headbangers Mosh & Thrasher Def Marc Mero & The Artist Formally Known As Goldust with Luna ** an ok matchMero told Sable to F off pretty much. Goldust was dressed Marylin Mansondust. Thrasher did an ok blade job during the match. BTW I hated The Marc Mero jealous of Sable storyline.Michael Cole interviewed Owen Hart he was asked if he can trust Stone Cold Steve Austin he said there will be no problems if Stone Cold stays out of his way. But there will be problems for Triple H cause he's going to bust up his legs.WWF Lightheavyweight ChampionshipChampion Taka Michinoku Def Pantera *** in a good match to retain the title.Brian Christopher came out to provide commentary with The King. Lawler said that JR has all girls but he got stood up at The Father Daughter Dance. After the match Brian Christopher tried to go after Taka Michinoku but he jumped them from the top rope & Taka made a run for it.Kevin Kelly interviewed Cactus Jack & Chainsaw Charlie in The A O L Room they were asked who they thought would replace Shawn Michaels in The 8 Man Tag Cactus Jack said he wanted revenge against The New Age Outlaws so he didn't care who replaced Shawn Michaels. Chainsaw Charlie had similar thoughts he said we have great partners he said what happened to them 2 weeks ago wasn't funny. They won't be laughing tonight.The Godwins Henry & Phineas Def The Quebecers Jacques Rougeau & Pierre Ouellet* & 3 quarters of a starThe King says he doesn't care for Canada but he hates Arkansas he also said that The Roto Rooter Man founded Canada. The Godwins pulled out a few actual wrestling moves off. Jim Ross said he didn't think that College Wrestling was big in Arkansas. He asked The King if he thought Bill Clinton was a wrestler in college. He responded by saying don't get me started on Bill Clinton where's Lee Harvey Oswald when the country needs him.This match was ok 1 of the better Godwin matches.Dok Hendrix interviewed The New Age Outlaws Jesse James said he didn't know who was going to replace Shawn Michaels & they weren't involved in the decision making. This wasn't much of an interview segment.Jim Ross talked to Jim Cornette about Jeff Jarrett's upcoming NWA North American title defense. They were asked if it would be 1 on 1 or a gang attack. Cornette said that Bradshaw needs to remember what happened when Jeff Jarrett put The Figure 4 on him it almost injured his knee's that's why he ain't in The NFL anymore. Jim Ross asked Jeff Jarrett if he was man enough to put The Figure 4 on Bradshaw by himself. Jarrett said he has perfected The Figure 4 Leg Lock.NWA North American ChampionshipBradshaw Def Champion Jeff Jarrett with Jim Cornette by disqualification ** so Jarrett retains the title. An ok match it would've been 2 & a quarter of a star of 2 & half stars had it had a winner. The NWA members came out to beat up Bradshaw but then The Road Warriors came down to run The NWA off.Michael Cole interviewed Triple H & Chyna Triple H said that every wrestler in the country has been calling cause DX is the number 1 franchise in Professional Wrestling. He added no 1 can replace Shawn Michaels so it will be 3 against 4.Ad shown for Wrestlemania XIV promoting Mike Tyson.Dok Hendrix interviewed The Nation Of Domination he asked about the issues The NOD have has as of late he wanted to ask the leader of The NOD The Rock took the mic but then Faarooq took it & told The Rock that he's begging for ana  s  s whoopin. He said that he pulls rank around here & he said when I say fall in they fall in.War Of Attrition 10 Man Tag Team MatchKen ShamrockAhmed Johnson& The DOAChainzShull & 8 BallDefThe Nation Of DominationFaarooq, The RockD'Lo BrownMark Henry& Kama Moustpha** another ok match this was Ahmed Johnson's last WWF appearanceAfter match The Rock & Faarooq had words The Rock shoved Faarooq & the rest of The Nation Of Domination held them back. The Rock walked off Faarooq tole him to get back in the ring they all gave The Nation Of Domination salute.Michael Cole interviewed Stone Cold Steve Austin who said he doesn't give 2 craps about who will replace Shawn Michaels & it's fun to whoop someone'sa  s  s in Texas.A great video package for The Vader Kane match was shown.Kane with Paul Bearer Def Big Van Vader ** & quarter of a star half decent match with 2 big men. After the match Kane took a big wrench & hit Vader in the face with it & Jim Ross said The Lord's name in vain lol.A really good ad for Wrestlemania XIV was shown.A vey good video package was shown for the now Non Sanction 8 Man Tag Team MatchNon Sanctioned No Holds Barred 8 Man Tag Team MatchStone Cold Steve AustinOwen HartCactus Jack & Chainsaw CharlieDefTriple HThe New Age Outlaws Road Dogg Jesse James & BA Billy Gunn& Savio Vega**** & half starsThis match was no classic but it was wild.After the match Chyna got in Austin's face & mouthed off to him she also shoved him but he started to leave but Chyna flipped him off & she earned herself a Stone Cold Stunner. Austin got on the mic & gave us an OhH  e  ll YEAH!for me this was a good follow up show. A good undercard nothing was under a star & 3 quarters. The Lightheavyweight title match was good. Kane & Vader did what it needed to it to give Kane another win to build up to Undertaker & Kane it was halfway decent match. The opener The Headbanger going over Marc Mero & Goldust was ok. The Godwins & Quebecer's match was ok. Jeff Jarrett vs Bradshaw was ok. The 10 Man Tag was ok & The 8 Man Tag Team No Holds Barred match was great.This show is youtube if you want to see & you can always buy it if you like it. Next review for a retro wrestling Pay Per View will be Wrestlemania XIV.
summary: WWF No Way Out Of Texas In Your House review 8/10
Title: WWF No Way Out! - In Your House VHS

reviewText: 1998 No Way outFebruary 15, 1998Compaq CentreHouston, TexasMarc Mero & Artist Formerly Known As Goldust V. HeadbangersOk opener that saw a catfight at the end that was almost better than the match itself...Or course i'm lying...but I'm having fun and that's the only important thing. Oh, by the way....the Bangers win. **WWF Light Heavyweight Championship:Taka Michinoku (Champion) V. PanteraGood match with alots of high flying action. Taka retains. ***1/4Quebecers V. GodwinnsZZZ...ZZZ...Oh I wake up just in time to see the Godwinns win. DUDNWA North American Championship:Jeff Jarrett (Champion) V. BradsahwGod I love Jarrett's music here, it's awesome. However, the match wasn't and it was just barely watchable. Bradsahw wins..what!...oh thank god by DQ. *War Of Attrition (Or Just A Simple 10-Man Tag Team Match...don't ask):Ken Shamrock, Ahmed Johnson, & DOAV.Nation Of Dominationok match that really had no point. Shamrock was feuding with Rock and Ahmed just continues his two year feud with Faarooq that had got me to catch up on some sleep and no one else was feuding with anyone. YThe match ends when Shamrocks team wins. **Vader V. KaneDecent match that was better than what I expected. Kane wins. ***Unsanctioned 8 Man Tag Team Match:Stone Cold Steve Austin, Owen Hart, Cactus Jack, & Chainsaw CharlieV.Triple H, Savio Vega, & New Age OutlawsAlots of action to start out than some cool spots here and there and then Austin stunners someone to win. ***3/4Overall, way too many tag team matches and I think Vince just whated to get everyone on the card, nice gesture, but, you don't need 3/4 of the people u have on this card. Sorry Vince
summary: This Isn't The Survivor Series!!!...There Shouldn't Be This Many Tag Team Matches on One Show!!!!
Title: WWF No Way Out! - In Your House VHS

reviewText: This was not the best ppv video the WWF has ever made but it wasn't the worst. It started off with Headbangers-vs-Marc Mero and Goldust. A good tag match but some of the stuff before and after it were more entertaining. Taka Michinoku-vs-Pantera was a good lightheavyweight match. I don't know why Sunny was there. Brian Christopher put Taka at odds doing some funny commentary with J.R. and his dad. Godwinns-vs-Quebecers was the sleep match of the night(skip it). Jeff Jarrett put the NWA north american title on the line against Bradshaw. JJ beat him thanks to Jim Cornette. A bunch of stuff involving the nwa being kicked away from the ring because they don't have manager licenses(wonder why tag team partners get to be at ringside(matt hardy w/ Jeff Hardy). The war of ??? was between N.O.D. and Ken Shamrock,Ahmed Johnson,chainz,D.o.A. It got boring at some points but got better at the end. Kane-vs-Vader was an alright match as well. Austin,Owen Hart,Cactus Jack-vs-HHH,N.A.O.,and Savio Vega(why is he in the main event) was a good match if you really think about. It just doesn't seem right with these guys and in the main event of a pay per view. No Way Out 1998 had its ups and downs but was a good ppv.
summary: No Way Out of a Good PPV.
Title: WWF No Way Out! - In Your House VHS
